{"word":"G4098 - πίπτω - píptō - pip'-to - Fail","slug":"G4098","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<strong>Original: </strong><span class=\"hebrewOrGreek\">πίπτω</span>"},{"paragraph":"<strong>Transliteration: </strong>píptō"},{"paragraph":"<strong>Phonetic: </strong>pip'-to"},{"paragraph":"<strong>Short Definition: </strong>Fail"},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<b>&#x03C0;&#x03B9;&#x0301;&#x03C0;&#x03C4;&#x03C9;, &#x03C0;&#x03B5;&#x0301;&#x03C4;&#x03C9; - pipto&#x0304;  peto&#x0304;</b> - <i>pip'-to, pet'-o</i><p/>The first is a reduplicated and contracted form of the second (which occurs only as an alternate in certain tenses); probably akin to <a href=\"#/G4072\">G4072</a> through the idea of <i>alighting</i>; to <i>fall</i> (literally of figuratively): - fail, fall (down), light on."},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<strong>Cognate:</strong> <a href=\"#/G1601\">G1601</a>, <a href=\"#/G2667\">G2667</a>, <a href=\"#/G3895\">G3895</a>, <a href=\"#/G3900\">G3900</a>, <a href=\"#/G4045\">G4045</a>, <a href=\"#/G4430\">G4430</a>, <a href=\"#/G4431\">G4431</a>"}]}